s=&quot;auto, (min-width: 720px) 720px&quot; /&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class=&quot;kg-gallery-image&quot;&gt; &lt;img decoding=&quot;async&quot; src=&quot;https://cdn.iannelson.uk/uploads/2023/08/107-0747_IMG.jpg&quot; width=&quot;1600&quot; height=&quot;1200&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; alt srcset=&quot;https://cdn.iannelson.uk/uploads/2023/08/1_107-0747_IMG.jpg 600w, https://cdn.iannelson.uk/uploads/2023/08/2_107-0747_IMG.jpg 1000w, https://cdn.iannelson.uk/uploads/2023/08/107-0747_IMG.jpg 1600w&quot; sizes=&quot;auto, (min-width: 720px) 720px&quot; /&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class=&quot;kg-gallery-image&quot;&gt; &lt;img decoding=&quot;async&quot; src=&quot;https://cdn.iannelson.uk/uploads/2023/08/107-0749_IMG.jpg&quot; width=&quot;1600&quot; height=&quot;1200&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; alt srcset=&quot;https://cdn.iannelson.uk/uploads/2023/08/1_107-0749_IMG.jpg 600w, https://cdn.iannelson.uk/uploads/2023/08/2_107-0749_IMG.jpg 1000w, https://cdn.iannelson.uk/uploads/2023/08/107-0749_IMG.jpg 1600w&quot; sizes=&quot;auto, (min-width: 720px) 720px&quot; /&gt; &lt;/div&gt;

Cona’ Mheall (978m)
Another long walk in and only a single munro bagged, in the mist and rain. Yuk!
